DM [BN] BOT 12-12-2022 14:43
You've responded to a summons from the Abbot of the Abbey in Krezk (more properly - The Abbey of Saint Markovia). A call was put out to adventurers for an expedition into the mountains. You gather on the road to Krezk, or perhaps in the town. The Abbey sits on top of the cliffs above Krezk. You make your up the switchback road that hugs the cliff that looms over the village. It's ten feet wide and covered with loose gravel and chunks of broken rock. The ascent is slow and somewhat treacherous, and the air grows colder as one nears the top. A fifteen-foot-high curtain wall joins the abbey's two wings. Behind its battlements, two guards stand at attention, their features obscured by fog. Below them, set into the wall, is a pair of ten-foot-tall, wooden doors reinforced with bands of steel. To the right of these doors, mounted on the wall, is a tarnished copper plaque. The plaque bears the abbey's name, under which appear these words: "May her light cure all illness." It quickly becomes apparent the "guards" on the wall are propped-up scarecrows that wear corroded chain shirts and clutch rusted spears. Through the door in the fog-filled courtyard is a person, hunched over with gardening tools, tilling the soil. He looks up with a tired, worn face, and an eye-patch over one eye. Something seems off. The more perceptive of you realize - it's his hands. He has two right hands! There are heavy scars on his left arm, where his wrist extends into a backwards hand - a second right hand. "Come, you must be the adventures the Abbot summoned. He's waiting for you," he says in a raspy voice.
